        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 4:39PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sabougla, or 15 miles east of Grenada, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pittsboro, Slate Springs, Bounds, Derma, Sabougla, Ellard, Vardaman,
Bruce, Shepherd, Skuna, Retreat, Dentontown, Big Creek, Slate Spring,
and Calhoun City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
